constructor.details: Constructor that initializes the RentModule contract.

params.drm: The address of the drm contract.
params.hub: The address of the hub contract.
params.registrant: The address of the registrant contract.

getModuleMetadataURI().details: Retrieves the metadata URI for the module.

isRegistered().details: Checks if the module is already registered in the module registry.

returns._0: True if the module is already registered, false otherwise.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params.params: The parameters for processing the action.

returns._0: bytes memory The result of the action.

registerCurrency(address).details: Registers an ERC20 currency to be used for rentals.

params.currencyAddress: The address of the ERC20 currency.

returns._0: bool True if the currency is successfully registered.

registerModule().details: Registers the RentModule as a PUBLICATION_ACTION_MODULE.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setModuleMetadataURI(string).details: Sets the metadata URI for the RentModule.

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Checks if the contract supports a specific interface.

params.interfaceID: The ID of the interface to check.

returns._0: bool True if the contract supports the interface, false otherwise.

terms(address,uint256).details: This function checks if the current timestamp is within the valid period (timelock) for the specified account and content ID. If the current time is within the allowed period, the terms are considered satisfied.

params.account: The address of the account being checked.
params.contentId: The content ID associated with the access terms.

returns._0: bool True if the terms are satisfied, false otherwise.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

terms(address,uint256).notice: Checks whether the terms (such as rental period) for an account and content ID are still valid.
